text: Alyssa Brown (born 11 May 1989) is a Canadian artistic gymnast. Brown competed at the 2006 Commonwealth Games where she won a silver medal in the vault event and a bronze medal in the team event. She also won two bronze medals at the 2005 Pan American Gymnastics Championships in the team and balance beam events. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Oakville, Ontario Category:Canadian female artistic gymnasts Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in gymnastics Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for Canada Category:Gymnasts at the 2006 Commonwealth Games
